## 1. üéØ Core Responsive Design Principles

### 1.1. Mobile-First Approach
Start with mobile design and progressively enhance for larger screens:
- Design for smallest screens first (320px width)
- Add complexity only when screen size allows
- Use `min-width` media queries (not `max-width`)
- Prioritize essential content and features

### 1.2. Fluid vs Adaptive Layouts
- **Fluid (Responsive)**: Layouts flow and adapt continuously
- **Adaptive**: Layouts snap to specific breakpoints
- **Hybrid**: Combine both approaches for optimal results

### 1.3. Content First
- Mobile users should access the same content as desktop
- No "mobile version" that hides important features
- Prioritize content hierarchy based on user needs
- Progressive disclosure for complex information

## 2. ‚úÖ DO (Recommended Practices)

### 2.1. Flexible Grid Systems

#### CSS Grid for Complex Layouts
- ‚úÖ **Use CSS Grid for page-level layouts**
- ‚úÖ **Define flexible grid tracks with minmax()**
- ‚úÖ **Use auto-fit and auto-fill for responsive columns**
- ‚úÖ **Combine grid with gap for consistent spacing**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Responsive grid that adapts automatically */
.grid-container {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 1.5rem;
  padding: 1rem;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Mobile-first grid with progressive enhancement */
.layout {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr; /* Mobile: single column */
  gap: 1rem;
}

@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .layout {
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; /* Tablet: 2 columns */
    gap: 1.5rem;
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .layout {
    grid-template-columns: 250px 1fr; /* Desktop: sidebar + main */
    gap: 2rem;
  }
}
```

#### Flexbox for Component Layouts
- ‚úÖ **Use Flexbox for one-dimensional layouts**
- ‚úÖ **Allow items to wrap with flex-wrap**
- ‚úÖ **Use flex-grow and flex-shrink appropriately**
- ‚úÖ **Combine with gap for spacing (modern browsers)**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Flexible navigation that adapts */
.nav {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1rem;
  align-items: center;
}

.nav-item {
  flex: 1 1 auto; /* Grow, shrink, auto basis */
  min-width: 120px; /* Prevent too-narrow items */
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Responsive card layout */
.card-container {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1rem;
}

.card {
  flex: 1 1 calc(100% - 1rem); /* Mobile: full width */
  min-width: 0; /* Allow flex items to shrink below content size */
}

@media (min-width: 640px) {
  .card {
    flex: 1 1 calc(50% - 1rem); /* Tablet: 2 columns */
  }
}

@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .card {
    flex: 1 1 calc(33.333% - 1rem); /* Desktop: 3 columns */
  }
}
```

### 2.2. Breakpoint Strategy

#### Standard Breakpoints
- ‚úÖ **Use common device breakpoints**
- ‚úÖ **Name breakpoints semantically**
- ‚úÖ **Keep breakpoints in CSS variables or config**
- ‚úÖ **Test between breakpoints, not just at exact values**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Standard breakpoint system */
:root {
  --breakpoint-sm: 640px;   /* Small devices (large phones) */
  --breakpoint-md: 768px;   /* Medium devices (tablets) */
  --breakpoint-lg: 1024px;  /* Large devices (desktops) */
  --breakpoint-xl: 1280px;  /* Extra large devices */
  --breakpoint-2xl: 1536px; /* Ultra-wide screens */
}

/* Mobile first: Base styles for mobile */
.container {
  width: 100%;
  padding: 1rem;
}

/* Tablet and up */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .container {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 1.5rem;
  }
}

/* Desktop and up */
@media (min-width: 1024px) {
  .container {
    max-width: 960px;
    padding: 2rem;
  }
}

/* Large desktop and up */
@media (min-width: 1280px) {
  .container {
    max-width: 1200px;
  }
}
```

#### Content-Based Breakpoints
- ‚úÖ **Add breakpoints where content breaks, not just at device sizes**
- ‚úÖ **Test with actual content, not lorem ipsum**
- ‚úÖ **Adjust typography at breakpoints**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Typography adjusts at content breakpoints */
.heading {
  font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
  line-height: 1.2;
}

/* Adjust when line length gets too long */
@media (min-width: 900px) {
  .text-content {
    max-width: 65ch; /* Optimal 50-75 characters per line */
    margin: 0 auto;
  }
}
```

### 2.3. Responsive Images

