### 2.5. Touch-Friendly Design

#### Tap Target Sizes
- ‚úÖ **Minimum 44√ó44px tap targets (iOS HIG)**
- ‚úÖ **48√ó48dp minimum (Android Material)**
- ‚úÖ **Add padding to increase target size**
- ‚úÖ **Space targets at least 8px apart**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Touch-friendly buttons */
.button {
  min-height: 44px;
  min-width: 44px;
  padding: 12px 24px;
  font-size: 1rem;
  /* Add visual feedback */
  transition: transform 100ms;
}

.button:active {
  transform: scale(0.98);
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Touch-friendly navigation */
.nav-link {
  display: block;
  padding: 16px 20px;
  min-height: 48px;
  /* Adequate spacing between links */
  margin: 4px 0;
}

/* ‚úÖ Good: Touch-friendly form inputs */
input,
select,
textarea {
  min-height: 44px;
  padding: 12px 16px;
  font-size: 16px; /* Prevents zoom on iOS */
  border: 2px solid #ccc;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* Increase touch targets for checkboxes/radio */
input[type="checkbox"],
input[type="radio"] {
  width: 24px;
  height: 24px;
  margin: 10px; /* Adds padding to touch area */
}
```

#### Gesture Support
- ‚úÖ **Support swipe gestures for carousels**
- ‚úÖ **Avoid hover-only interactions**
- ‚úÖ **Provide touch feedback (ripple, scale)**
- ‚úÖ **Test on actual touch devices**

```css
/* ‚úÖ Good: Touch-friendly carousel */
.carousel {
  overflow-x: auto;
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
